  <static seed="1181" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalExpressionAlgebraSkills/multiplyRationalExpressions50.pg">
    <statement><p>Simplify this expression, and if applicable, write the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{t^{2}-7t+6}{t-4}} \cdot {\frac{4t-16}{t-1}} =}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>4\mathopen{}\left(t-6\right), t\ne 1\hbox{ and }t\ne 4</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{t^{2}-7t+6}{t-4}} \cdot {\frac{4t-16}{t-1}} 
      \amp = \frac{{\left(t-1\right)\mathopen{}\left(t-6\right)}}{{t-4}} \cdot \frac{{4\mathopen{}\left(t-4\right)}}{{t-1}} \\
      \amp = {4\mathopen{}\left(t-6\right), t\ne 1\hbox{ and }t\ne 4}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factors <m>t - 1</m> and <m>t - 4</m> were canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>t \ne {1, 4}</m>.</p>
</solution>
